<subSubSection id="97EA653FFFF978016FE6FF15FF68FD71" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DF4F36B4FFF978016FE6FF15FED0FDE5" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016FE6FF15FE60FF68" bold="true" box="[199,463,150,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016EF7FF14FC8BFF68" authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2022" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2022" box="[470,804,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenigmatista" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016EF7FF14FC8BFF68" box="[470,804,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">Austronausibius aenigmatista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016C0DFF14FC29FF69" bold="true" box="[812,902,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F6B757DDFFF978016C0DFF14FC29FF69" box="[812,902,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from extant congeners by a combination of characters: lateral pronotal sides with six obvious denticles (in contrast to one obvious denticle at anterior angle and other lateral denticles indicated by slight undulations in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016CD8FF5CFB2CFF21" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[1017,1155,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edentatus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016CD8FF5CFB2CFF21" box="[1017,1155,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. edentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), pronotal disc without a shallow depression and median ridge (in contrast to shallow pronotal impression and little-developed median ridge in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016F96FEA4FE9AFE99" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[183,309,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aemulus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016F96FEA4FE9AFE99" box="[183,309,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. aemulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), metafemur without a denticle (in contrast to metafemur with a denticle in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016B8DFEA4FB58FE99" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[1196,1271,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leai">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016B8DFEA4FB58FE99" box="[1196,1271,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. leai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), setal pattern without herringbone arrangement (in contrast to elytra with herringbone pattern of setae on 3rd or 5th and alternate interstriae in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016E0BFEECFEDCFE51" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[298,371,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leai">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016E0BFEECFEDCFE51" box="[298,371,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. leai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016E88FEECFD9FFE50" authorityName="Olliff" authorityYear="1886" box="[425,560,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Silvanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congener">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016E88FEECFD9FFE50" box="[425,560,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. congener</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), pronotal disc evenly convex, not impressed (in contrast to pronotal disc with weak impressions in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016EA7FE10FDADFE74" baseAuthorityName="Grouvelle" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[390,514,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016EA7FE10FDADFE74" box="[390,514,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. wagneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species), epipleuron with three rows of tubercles basally (in contrast to 
<quantity id="18089B51FFF978016FB6FE35FF72FE09" box="[151,221,438,465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.143" metricValueMax="1.27" metricValueMin="1.016" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" unit="in" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016FC3FE34FEF2FE09" baseAuthorityName="Blackburn" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[226,349,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aridulus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016FC3FE34FEF2FE09" box="[226,349,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. aridulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<quantity id="18089B51FFF978016EB3FE35FE78FE09" box="[402,471,438,465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.397" metricValueMax="1.524" metricValueMin="1.27" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" unit="in" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016EFCFE34FDCAFE09" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[477,613,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016EFCFE34FDCAFE09" box="[477,613,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and narrower metanepisternum, 
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016CC0FE34FBABFE08" box="[993,1028,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">i.e.</emphasis>
, epipleuron widest point about twice as wide as adjacent region of metanepisternum (in contrast to wide metanepisternum in 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016B4AFE58FB5BFE2D" authorityName="Halstead" authorityYear="1980" box="[1131,1268,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016B4AFE58FB5BFE2D" box="[1131,1268,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Additionally, the rounded form of antennomere 11 (without a small process apically) distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016B71FE7CFB50FDC0" authority="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs, 2022" authorityName="Alekseev &amp; Bukejs" authorityYear="2022" box="[1104,1279,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Austronausibius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenigmatista" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016B71FE7CFB50FDC0" box="[1104,1279,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">A. aenigmatista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016A27FE7CFAF0FDC1" bold="true" box="[1286,1375,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F6B757DDFFF978016A27FE7CFAF0FDC1" box="[1286,1375,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from all extant congeners.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF4F36B4FFF978016FE6FDC4FF68FD71" blockId="5.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
The new species resembles 
<emphasis id="ED84EAA6FFF978016D24FDC4FDD3FDB8" box="[517,636,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="142">
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016D24FDC4FDF1FDB8" authorityName="Alekseev et Bukejs" authorityYear="2016" box="[517,606,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" genus="Mistran" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mistran</taxonomicName>
ot
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BB614B45FFF978016DA2FDC4FC09FDB9" author="Alekseev, V. I. &amp; Bukejs, A." box="[643,934,583,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" pagination="101 - 108" refId="ref4703" refString="Alekseev, V. I. &amp; Bukejs, A. (2016) New fossil genus of Silvanidae (Insecta: Coleoptera) from Baltic amber (Tertiary, Eocene). Zootaxa, 4144 (1), 101 - 108. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4144.1.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Alekseev et Bukejs, 2016</bibRefCitation>
from Baltic amber but can be distinguished from it and all other extinct mid-late Eocene 
<taxonomicName id="18F04D37FFF978016DBCFDE8FCBCFD5D" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" box="[669,787,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Silvanidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Silvanidae</taxonomicName>
representatives using the identification key provided below.
</paragraph>
